fields.day1_exercises:
Warm-up: 10-15 minutes of walking or light jogging

Bench Press (Barbell): 4 sets, 8-10 reps
Incline Dumbbell Press: 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Chest Fly (Cable): 3 sets, 10-12 reps
Dips (Assisted if needed): 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Tricep Pushdown (Cable): 3 sets, 12 reps
Overhead Tricep Extension (Dumbbell): 3 sets, 12 reps

Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of chest and tricep stretches
fields.day2_exercises:
Warm-up: 10-15 minutes on a stationary bike or brisk walking

Squats (Barbell): 4 sets, 8-10 reps
Leg Press: 4 sets, 10-12 reps
Lunges (Dumbbells): 3 sets, 10 reps per leg
Leg Curl (Machine): 3 sets, 12 reps
Leg Extension (Machine): 3 sets, 12 reps
Plank: 3 sets, 30-45 seconds
Russian Twists: 3 sets, 20 reps

Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of leg and ab stretches
fields.day3_exercises:
Warm-up: 10-15 minutes of jogging or stationary bike

Lat Pulldown (Wide Grip): 4 sets, 8-10 reps
Barbell Row: 4 sets, 8-10 reps
Seated Cable Row: 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Shoulder Press (Dumbbells): 3 sets, 8-10 reps
Lateral Raise (Dumbbells): 3 sets, 10-12 reps
Face Pulls (Cable): 3 sets, 12 reps

Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of back and shoulder stretches
fields.notes:
The focus in this program is on compound exercises to build mass and strength, ensuring you target multiple muscle groups in each session.
Always warm up before starting your workout and cool down after each session with proper stretching.
Choose a weight that challenges you, especially in the last 2-3 reps of each set.
Rest between sets should be 60-90 seconds for optimal results.
If you experience any pain or discomfort, stop immediately and consult a professional.
